# ARIA & behavior (Templ registry)

See [`docs/aria.md`](../../docs/aria.md) for the long-form contract.

## Three layers

Do not collapse these layers:

| Layer | Owner | Rule |
|-------|-------|------|
| Static semantics | registry | valid SSR HTML without JS |
| Explicit ARIA props | brick API | typed `Aria*` props in `*.spec.md` |
| Behavior hooks | app runtime | opt-in `Behavior` / `DataUI8Kit` only |

The registry emits markup contracts. `@ui8kit/aria` owns focus management,
keyboard routing, open/close state sync, and APG-style client behavior.

## Static markup (library)

Use **`github.com/fastygo/templ/utils`** helpers in brick `.templ` files:

- `AriaLabel`, `AriaExpanded`, `AriaControls`, `AriaCurrent`, `AriaModal`, …
- `ControlAttrs`, `SwitchAttrs`, `MergeAttrs`, `DOMAttrs`
- Component-specific typed props: `AriaLabelledBy`, `AriaDescribedBy`, …

Declare required a11y fields in `*.spec.md` `api:` with roles such as `accessible-name`, `state`.

Default bricks emit **SSR-safe** HTML without a client runtime.

## Behavior hooks (opt-in)

| Prop | Bricks | When set |
|------|--------|----------|
| `DataUI8Kit` | `Dialog`, `Nav`, `Breadcrumb`, … | emits `data-ui8kit="…"` |
| `Behavior: "ui8kit"` | `Sheet` family | emits `data-ui8kit-dialog*` hooks |

When empty / default: **no** behavior attributes. Library stays framework-neutral.

Do not implement custom widget JavaScript in `ui/` or `components/`. Add or
register the needed APG pattern in the consuming app through `@ui8kit/aria`.

## Sheet contract

`Sheet` is a side panel using the `@ui8kit/aria` dialog pattern:

- root is `<div role="dialog">`, not native `<dialog>`;
- root uses `hidden` and `data-state` for visibility state;
- `behavior="ui8kit"` emits `data-ui8kit="sheet"` and
  `data-ui8kit-dialog`;
- trigger / close / overlay parts use `data-ui8kit-dialog-open`,
  `data-ui8kit-dialog-close`, and `data-ui8kit-dialog-target`;
- React `open` is initial SSR state only when `behavior="ui8kit"` is active.

Native centered `Dialog` remains separate and may use native `<dialog>`.

## Examples preview only

`examples/` loads a **dialog-only** `@ui8kit/aria` bundle so Sheet demos work in the browser:

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `examples/scripts/ui8kit-entry.mjs` | Registers `dialog` pattern |
| `examples/web/static/js/ui8kit.js` | Built bundle (`bun run build:js`) |
| `examples/web/static/js/manifest.json` | Pattern manifest |

After changing hooks in **examples** or upgrading `@ui8kit/aria`:

```bash
cd examples && bun run build:js
bun run validate:aria
```

`validate:aria` scans **`examples/`** markup against the manifest — not the whole module tree unless extended.

## Authoring rules

- Icon-only controls in showcase **must** include `AriaLabel` in spec + `*.data.json`.
- Do not enable `Behavior: "ui8kit"` in default brick showcase unless demonstrating client wiring.
- Prefer typed `Aria*` props over dumping aria-* into `Attrs`.
- Document root element and `semantics` in `*.spec.md`.

## Dual-stack note

Templ and React ports must match static semantics and documented behavior-hook
attributes. For Sheet, the `ui8kit` DOM contract is intentionally identical
across both runtimes.
